</small></small></td></tr></tbody></table><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><table style="text-align: left; width: 823px; height: 151px;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td style="white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: top;"><br><table style="text-align: left; width: 277px; height: 73px;" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2"><tbody><tr><td valign="top"><big><big><big><big><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(204, 204, 204);">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span><small><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 0);"> &nbsp; Events</span></small><span style="color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"></span></span></big></big></big></big></td></tr></tbody></table><br><br><br></td><td><small style="font-weight: bold;"><small style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><font size="2"><small><br></small></font><span style="font-style: italic;"></span></small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-style: italic;">2010 October 02</span>&nbsp;&nbsp; 113th FFA monthly interclub practice at MAC dojo</span></small><small><span style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br><br></span><small><span style="text-decoration: line-through; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span></small><font style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;" size="5"><small>Important: major change of plans (as of 2010 September 30)</small></font></small><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">There has been a major change in plans for this Saturday's interclub practice, as follows:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">1) </span><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Venue change</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">: The venue shall be the Makati Aikido Club dojo at Makati Sports Club, and NOT Club 650 in Libis.</span> <span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Click <a href="../FindUs/findus.html">here</a> for street directions and map.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">2) </span><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Format change</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">:
 The special format that had been previously announced, involving 
multiple instructors and an enbukai, shall NOT be implemented this 
Saturday. Instead, this shall be postponed to the November interclub 
practice. Details to be announced soon. The format for Saturday, October
 02, shall be the regular format for monthly interclub practices.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">3) </span><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Hosting change</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">:
 The host for this Saturday's interclub
 reverts back to the original rotation schedule, which states that the 
host for October is JBAC. Adrian Gan shall lead the interclub practice.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">4) </span><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">What happens to the originally planned big celebration?</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
 The big celebration of the 10th anniversary of the monthly interclub 
practice tradition has been reset to the first Saturday of November 
(Nov. 06). Please watch for details soon.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Please disregard all 
previous messages, website announcements, or Facebook announcements that
 are inconsistent with #1 through #4 above. As of 2010 September 30, the above supersede the crossed-out text below.</span></small><br><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;"><br><br>Saturday, October 2 will not be the usual interclub training. It will </span></small><font style="text-decoration: line-through;" size="2"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);"><span style="color: black;">be the 113th monthly FFA interclub, but it will</span>&nbsp;</span></span></font><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;">also be a celebration of a significant milestone. </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;">October
 2010 marks the 10th year anniversary of the FFA monthly interclub 
training events. A special instruction format and enbukai 
(demonstration) are being planned. Keep visiting this page for more 
details, which will be posted as soon as they are
 known.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;">Details known so far:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: line-through;"></small><small style="text-decoration: line-through;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br>THIS MONTH'S VENUE:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">ACP Dojo</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Club 650<br>Libis, C5, Marikina<br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"></span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">DATE AND TIME:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Saturday, 2010 October 02</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">1830 
hrs (6:30 p.m.)</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(For easier recall, interclub practice always starts 
at 6:30 p.m. regardless of venue.)</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"></span></font></span></small><font style="text-decoration: line-through;" size="2"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">PRACTITIONERS
FROM NON-AFFILIATED DOJOS VERY WELCOME. For more details, e-mail
<span style="border-bottom: 2px dotted rgb(54, 99, 136); background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 50%; -moz-background-clip: initial; -moz-background-origin: initial; -moz-background-inline-policy: initial; cursor: pointer;" class="yiv322818728yiv1608554077yiv898408284yshortcuts" id="yiv322818728yiv1608554077yiv898408284lw_1283069715_1">macaikido@yahoo.com</span> or call 890-1976 (Marlene or Barbi).</span></font><font size="2"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
  <br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
</font> 
